Johannesburg – The South African Broadcasting Corporation (SABC) did not broadcast the do or die match between Bafana Bafana and Sudan. The SABC said in a tweet, “The SABC can confirm that the public service broadcaster couldn’t secure the broadcasting rights of the match between the Bafana and Sudan due to the exorbitant costs and as a result this match will not be aired on any of the SABC platforms.” Fans were left disappointed and took to Twitter to share their views on the troubled broadcaster.  Take a look at what they said on Twitter below:        You may also be interested in: Fans show concern after seeing Babes Wodumo with a ‘baby bump’ sip champagne Follow @SundayWorldZA on Twitter and @sundayworldza on Instagram, or like our Facebook Page, Sunday World, by clicking here for the latest breaking news in South Africa. To Subscribe to Sunday World, click here. 